re tax payers money has been thrown into education over last decade than ever before and yet the problem is worse. I think you get rid of the unions and the federal government involvement. Honestly though you will never &quot;fix&quot; the public school system because the people with  the real power the ones who pay the bills don't speak up or take back control.I mean the voters. Until we get control of the education system back under states and local government. Until the voters can put the people who really care for the future generations of this country and are held accountable. Until we can get the kids away from the electronic gadgets and back to teaching the basics in schools. Until everyone begins to care, Parents, teachers, elected officials, and most important the kids then public schools will never turn things around. So all the money, programs, conventions,town hall meetings in the universe will not fix the public schools.  So if you can afford private school or home school go for it. If your kid's are in public schools then get involved to make sure they are given the best they can get. Push them to be the best they can be. Make damn sure you know what they are being taught in your schools and make your voices heard if they are not. Don't listen to Allison Benedikt, it's not about money but it is about action and working together by the voters. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1666" language="en" documentId="2487" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="NoNewsHere" date="Aug 29, 2013 9:24PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="10" thumbsDown="0" origId="2487" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1666"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>